{"id": 100550, "acmi_id": "181519", "title": "IMAX", "title_annotation": "", "slug": "imax", "creator_credit": "", "credit_line": "", "headline_credit": "", "thumbnail": {"image_url": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P179567_Imax3DGlasses_34.jpg.1200x1200_q85.jpg", "has_video": false}, "record_type": "group", "type": "Film", "is_on_display": true, "last_on_display_place": "ACMI: Gallery 1", "last_on_display_date": "2031-02-16", "is_context_indigenous": false, "material_description": "", "unpublished": false, "first_production_date": null, "brief_description": "<p>More than 50 years since it debuted at EXPO ‘67 in Montreal, IMAX has become synonymous with cinematic innovation, championed by pioneering filmmakers like Christopher Nolan, James Cameron and J.J. Abrams.</p>", "constellations_primary": [{"id": 181, "name": "Big screen dreams", "description": "With groundbreaking technology and a unique cinema experience, today IMAX theatres are not only loved by audiences but championed by pioneering filmmakers like Christopher Nolan and James Cameron. Yet the route to get there was an unconventional one."}], "constellations_other": [], "recommendations": [], "title_for_label": "<p>IMAX</p>", "creator_credit_for_label": "", "headline_credit_for_label": "", "description": "<p>It started as an experiment, with Canadian filmmakers Graeme Ferguson, Roman Kroiter and Robert Kerr setting out to see if they could make a massive, multi-screen experience. Famously the group pulled off the complicated task of syncing nine film projectors to create a large screen installation. More than 50 years since it debuted at EXPO ‘67 in Montreal, IMAX has become synonymous with cinematic innovation. Championed by pioneering filmmakers like Christopher Nolan, James Cameron and J.J. Abrams, it has come a long way from its early reputation as the home of nature documentaries. With a combination of stadium seating, giant curved screens, immersive sound and 70mm film projection, its unique viewing experience has seen IMAX theatres established all over the world.</p>", "description_for_label": ["<p>It started as an experiment, with Canadian filmmakers Graeme Ferguson, Roman Kroiter and Robert Kerr setting out to see if they could make a massive, multi-screen experience. Famously the group pulled off the complicated task of syncing nine film projectors to create a large screen installation. More than 50 years since it debuted at EXPO ‘67 in Montreal, IMAX has become synonymous with cinematic innovation. Championed by pioneering filmmakers like Christopher Nolan, James Cameron and J.J. Abrams, it has come a long way from its early reputation as the home of nature documentaries. With a combination of stadium seating, giant curved screens, immersive sound and 70mm film projection, its unique viewing experience has seen IMAX theatres established all over the world.</p>"], "credit_line_for_label": "", "details": [{"label": "Curatorial section", "display_values": ["The Story of the Moving Image&nbsp;→ Moving Pictures&nbsp;→ 08. Immersive Innovations&nbsp;→ MI-08-C01"]}], "stats": {"tap_count": 1986}, "links": [], "creators_primary": [], "creators_other": [], "video_links": [], "media_note": null, "images": [{"id": 12171, "image_file": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P179567_Imax3DGlasses_34.jpg", "image_file_thumbnail": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P179567_Imax3DGlasses_34.jpg.1200x1200_q85.jpg", "image_file_xs": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P179567_Imax3DGlasses_34.jpg.480x480_q85.jpg", "image_file_s": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P179567_Imax3DGlasses_34.jpg.960x960_q85.jpg", "image_file_m": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P179567_Imax3DGlasses_34.jpg.1920x1920_q85.jpg", "image_file_l": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/P179567_Imax3DGlasses_34.jpg.3840x3840_q85.jpg", "caption": "P179567_Imax3DGlasses_34", "credit_line": "Photograph by Egmont Contr